public interface IParameterizable
extends IModuleInfo

ModuleInfoClass interface for parameterizable modules.
A module is parameterizable if arguments can be passed to it when being instantiated.

Method Detail

newInstance

public IModule newInstance(java.lang.Object[] args)
Must create a new instance of the ModuleClass with given arguments.

Note: Never instantiate modules directly via their constructor(s) or via IModuleInfo.newInstance! Instead it is highly recommended to use the ModuleFactory class to create and dispose module instances.

Parameters:
args - The arguments for the new instance.
Returns:
The newly created module instance as IModule.
See Also:
ModuleFactory.newInstance(ModuleContainer, Object[])
